Wings reward design

The reward system should celebrate movement and reliability, not volume.

Why wings

Halo implies virtue in a vague moral sense.
Wings imply:
	•	motion
	•	carrying
	•	bridging distance
	•	service between places

It is visually and conceptually correct.

Types of wings

Courier Wings
Earned for successful forwarding of mail toward destinations.

Postmaster Wings
Earned for running stable hubs, maintaining uptime, serving cached mail reliably.

Bridge Wings
Earned when a node meaningfully connects otherwise separated clusters.

Storm Wings
Earned for successful carriage during outages, degraded networks, or emergency mode.

Memory Wings
Earned for preserving important public artifacts, directory shards, and address books.

Anti-gaming principles

Do not reward:
	•	raw bytes forwarded
	•	raw message count
	•	self-sent loops
	•	repeated duplicate forwarding
	•	spam relays
	•	easy same-room churn

Instead reward:
	•	unique useful deliveries
	•	path-shortening contribution
	•	successful custody transfer
	•	persistence over time
	•	delivery under adversity
	•	validated bridge service between distinct trust/locality zones

A relay only gets credit when its participation was actually needed.

Wings accounting

Each artifact can carry a limited "reward budget" split across contributing nodes.
For example:
	•	sender funds a tiny voluntary reward
	•	recipient or community fund can add more
	•	network grants emergency bonus in outage mode

Credit is split by actual contribution:
	•	hub that stored it for 6 days during outage
	•	courier phone that carried it into village
	•	local handset that delivered to recipient

This prevents infinite minting.

⸻

System modes

The system should adapt behavior based on observed conditions.

1. Optimistic mode

Assume internet mostly works.
	•	low redundancy
	•	prefer direct routes
	•	use hubs for efficiency
	•	smaller cache windows
	•	quick pruning

2. Partition mode

Assume clusters may be cut off for hours or days.
	•	higher redundancy
	•	retain address/routing summaries longer
	•	preload locality mail
	•	encourage multi-hop custody copies

3. Crisis mode

Assume regional outage or intentional shutdown.
	•	maximum store-and-forward
	•	prioritize family, emergency, and directory messages
	•	compress aggressively
	•	preserve power
	•	allow delayed batched sync
	•	reward bridging strongly

